caption: Nothing great. Food is just okay, cocktails are decent. Overall nothing special.

Amazing!! I felt so great about eating indoors during the pandemic at LaBrasa! the team has done anexcellent job making the place feel cozy, safe and of course the food is always delicious!! Thank you LaBrasa for making me feel a bit "normal" in these abnormal times
Great food, service and atmosphere
Food and service was so good. Try anything with the salsa macha on it!
NYC quality restaurant in Sommerville! Great service, 10/10 food, big portions. Author cusine with a latin american taste.
This is a nice little neighborhood joint.  The drinks are great and the food that I've had has been decent as well.  I hope they stick around.

I went with my husband for dinner since we could not travel for our honeymoon. The atmosphere was perfect, rustic and cozy. The staff were all very friendly and had good recommendations for meals and drinks. The flan is a delicious combination of smokey and sweet that is indulgent. You can share it or have it all for yourself. My thanks for making a special day Amazing!!
Perfect cocktails, always a good place for oysters, and everything else is great too.

The food is delicious; the atmosphere is so refreshing; the cocktails are perfect- but also, the team here is amazing!! We have had so many wonderful experiences working with them for weddings and events and then some of the best dining and brunch experiences during those elusive nights off.  We definitely highly recommend la Brasa!
Always amazing food
Gorgeous restaurant, lovely staff but the food is very exotic Mexican food and my daughter could not eat the food it was sooo spicey. The service was fast and our waitress was so very nice to us.
This is my new favorite place in Somerville. Everything on their menu is incredible. Highly recommend the duck confit! The mole it comes with is wonderful.  Great atmosphere, perfect for a date.
Everything we had here was excellent: drinks, salad, mole...all were incredible!
Delicious oysters, good South American food.

(Translated by Google) They do not speak my language .. And they do not care about Hispanics despite grilled Hispanic word ..  (Original) No hablan mi idioma.. Y no les importan los hispanos a pesar de que la brasa es palabra hispana..
Great food, atmosphere just amazing.  A must for brunch.
Everything was awesome! The food was really good, with sizeable portions for sharing. The cocktails were creative and very tasty. Overall, highly recommended.
Solid quality food and drinks. This place is casual and has a lovely ambience. The chicken main course is so tender and has well balanced flavors. Would visit again!

I just had my 30th birthday dinner at La Brasa and have only good things to say. I had a group of 25 people and La Brasa accommodated my large group's requests. The service, food, environment were all great! I have only positive things to say about La Brasa and look forward to going back again.

Food was ok. I got the pork shank and it had no flavor. The shank was steaming hot on one side, cold on another. Very bland. Friend got the Ribeye and it was cold also.  Service was good. Waiter was very nice.
Great nuevo latino food selection!

OMG! Amazing. Visited this evening and everything was great. The food was served promptly. I had the duck confit which comes with a rich mole sauce. Drinks could be better but other than that, great food great environment.

You walk in and are immediately welcomed with the warm smell of the wood oven, cool greenery and cozy decorations! This paired with $1 oyster special was exactly what we needed on a cold fall day. The food and service were excellent, and we stayed and dined for quite some time.  My favorites were the lamb tostada and the tacos for appetizers. The swordfish and the duck entrees were amazing- served in a creamy sauce and mole sauce respectively, and very nicely arranged! Great decor and atmosphere and great food!

I love La Brasa! Not only was the food amazing, but the staff was so kind and helpful throughout the wedding day. As a photographer, La Brasa is a refreshing and unique spot full of cool photos spots. It's perfect for an intimate wedding!
I ordered the $20 meatball dish. It is on salty side， five small meatball. Small portion. The group is over 20 people so the 20 percent tip is mandatory.
Good food, great service!
I love la brasa. A great somerville classic for cocktails and food. Also tres leches is bomb

Food was mediocre at best. I ordered the swordfish my girl ordered the tamales both were extremely dry. Let me stress that the swordfush is served in a bowl of white sauce at it was overcooked and bone dry. The tamales were also very dry. The swordfish is served in a white sauce that had no seasoning. Although the small portions of pork belly as part of the swordfish main was very flavorful. And the seasoned tomatoes with the tamales was also tasty. The drinks were great in flavor but were skimpy on the booze.  I did express to the waitstaff that both entrees were very overcooked and dry. She did give us a free desert. I didnt make a fuss it was just given to us. The dessert was the only flavorful part of the meal. Verry overpriced for the food. There are many many (like over 10) authentic mexican and south american restaurants on the same street that have way better food for a fraction of the cost that actually know how to season their dishes. I would say that this restaurant is a waste of time considering thier area and type of food. I will also add for 24$ for less than 4 oz of swordfish is very skimpy. The three giant chuncks of uncooked celery on my main was a waste i didnt order buffalo wings.

So I went here once and was not impressed. I live nearby, and saw that they have $1 oysters between 5-6. I decided to try it again, and went in with my boyfriend to have dinner there. We ordered oysters, with several appetizers and drinks. We like to eat tapas style. The bill came out to about $70. But the waitress basically ruined the meal for us. What felt like every 10 minutes, she would come over and try to pressure us to buy 'mains.' We said we were ordering appetizers and she came back again and again to ask if we'd changed our minds and wanted mains. It was incredibly annoying and felt like she was shaming us for enjoying the $1 oyster offer and wanted us to order more so she could get a larger tip. It was bizarre and I couldn't get the word mains out of my head for like a day
Had a birthday breakfast there. Good

My first time visiting, what a disappointment the food had great presentation, but lacked flavor. Service was terrible, a fly flew into our plate, we told the server his response was "ok thank you for letting me know", cleared the table and came back with our $52.45 bill. No sorry, no nothing at their prices I was expecting a good fly free dining experience! NOT in this case!

I love this venue! I had the pleasure of DJing a wedding for David & Missy recently, and I was very impressed! Very cool interior design, amazing food, and flawlessly accommodating. If you are looking for a classy, cozy and interesting place to have a wedding, or simply out for dining, I highly recommend La Brasa! As a wedding DJ, this is a place that has found a special place in my memory. Excellent work! Cheers!!! ~ DJ Chillin McMillin
Great fresh food.
Great flavor, great service, dope music playlist!

Been here 3 times, once for dinner, twice for brunch. Attached picture is of steak and eggs and the pancake. All three times the food has been amazing. It's a bit pricey but the quality of the food is great

I like this place. It's one of those, if I lived in the neighborhood, I'd be there all the time spots. I've been here 2x - with 1.5 years between visits (l live in Seattle), and have been fairly impressed by the food both times.  This round, opted for the striped bass, and fried chicken wing in mesquite brown butter - a must have. The meal was pricey. But I won't hold that against them. It was also delicious. When in Rome. Or Boston.
Love the food...great oysters

Over rated  I’ve been there with a colleague, it wasn’t our first choice, but this restaurant has been highly recommended to us. We’ve been deceived: The service was OK, not good, OK. I had the Scallops crudo, which were amazing, but my carnitas tacos weren’t good and very very small. I had a glass of wine and they pour it at the bar, couldn’t see what they poured in my glass :s Nice decoration, nice neighborhood. I won’t go back and wouldn’t recommend the place.
Bartenders are knowledgeable and super nice!
Amazing wood fired grill, great staff.
Fantastic food, great atmosphere - strongly suggest happy hour oysters
Lovely atmosphere! Great service and very knowledgeable and helpful staff. Food was amazing. Many great flavors and aromas. A very pleasant pleasant place to have a nice meal
My brother held his wedding dinner rehearsal there. Food and drinks were amazing. Jake and Scott did an amazing job waiting on our party. A big Texas Thank You!!!
Everything about this place is amazing. The service is friendly, welcoming, and kind. The style of this restaurant is trendy and unique. And the food and drinks are way too good! Love it here

For the price I think the shared plates were awesome and the winners for me at the dinner service. The bread is phenomenal. The star appetizers were the chicken wing, ceviche, oysters, and the empanada. We were disappointed in our mains, which was the chicken and the branzino.  If I went back I would not get a main, but would stick with the shared plates.

Awesome place. Sometimes they have $1 oysters from 5pm to 6pm, and they were some of the best I've ever had. A lot of really interesting dishes. We just got a bunch of shared plates and some bread with two of their delicious spreads. Cocktails were really good and our server was super attentive. Highly recommend.
The bartenders alone make me wanna come back!  They know their stuff and are true mixologists!!
Had dollar oysters from 5-6, fresh and tasty, and some incredibly delicious coconut cocktail, plus spicy roast Brussels sprouts in a sweet syrup that were quite good.
Solid tasting food.

My fiance and I went to La Brasa for Valentine's Day. We asked for salt and pepper once our food came out and after putting salt on everything realized that we had been given sugar instead. Not wanting to be jerks about it we kindly let our waitress know about the mistake and rather than apologizing she joked 'oh you wanted salt?'. We weren't offered replacement meals or given a discount on our bill. Needless to say I was incredibly disappointed in the service. I really can't comment on the quality of most of the food because it was covered in sugar but the few appetizers we had before the sugar came out were quite good.

I never write reviews but for this particular experience I kinda had to. To start off, 3 of us order drinks. I order a very easy simple drink, a coke with lemon. Our waitress for some reason, as this was a hard drink to make said “I have to check if we can make it”. First off, what are you making? The lemon? The coke? I don’t know. Then my friend and wife orders their drinks. Moscow Mule tasted like a limeade, not a drip of alcohol. Shirley Temple was pretty much all grenadine. The menu was very confusing to understand. I understand it’s a tapas style restaurant but give more options for people that live in the area that can afford. I order the Tacos Carnitas and honestly the tacos looked just sad. Not only that but it’s one 2 for $10. If I pay that much. Fill it with meat. There was more salsa and sauce than meat. My friend orders the fried potatoes and it comes with a sauce, which she dropped and I know, our fault, we were very sorry and offered to clean but the waitress cleaned. However, as my friend went to use the bathroom, the waitress cleaned it with my friends napkin ... why? AND she never gave her a clean one back. We had to ask for it. Anyways, this place was just a downer. I know we have bad days and it’s Sunday, few hours before you close but doesn’t give you the right to be so serious. $116 later, the only thing that was appealing was the oysters. But than again, how can you mess that up! I love trying out my local places being from Somerville and living around. But I’d choose a different Mexican place around broadway, with a lot better and cheaper authentic food.

The food is really good, but it’s very expensive and the portions are small and not filling.  I ordered what I could afford, and the server kinda shamed us for not ordering more. I’m not sure who in the community this restaurant is supposed to serve. It’s way out of reach for people that live around here.

Order anything off the wood grill and pair it with some of the excellent sides on offer. If it's the shrimp you order, be forewarned that you'll get "el bicho entero. " If you're all about maximizing flavor and crunch maybe that's even a plus for you. For me it was just good presentation. The "humo" is the best mezcal cocktail I've had yet in the Boston area.
Delish seasonal cocktails, delightful bartenders and servers, divine food and dreamy ambiance! All you need on a cold winter evening
Very good Latin American food. And one of few places in Boston I've had a good quality old fashion with Oaxaca.
Excellent fare of grilled meats carefully prepared seafood, and coriously delicious starters. The only nit is that they charge too much for bread that has to be ordered separately
Food not great.  Tequila top shelf.  Depends on what you're after.

Overpriced, Wait staff and those working there looked sad, food portions vs. Price is way out of wack.  My husband got the meat cut at the table $32 - it tasted great but all he got was a bowl of meat! Don't buy the whole fish $30.  It was a flat fish with avocado and some pita bread. It was a total rip off.  No side dishes with meals. You had to buy them.  We weren't even offered a second drink.  I gave them a courtesy 10% tip only because my husband made me. I will never go back there again and I would advise those looking for a new restaurant to try out - not do try this one unless your just looking to throw money away.

We chose La Brasa as the venue for our company holiday party and everything was just perfect! The staff was a pleasure to work with, the food was great, the drinks were great, and the vibe was amazing - it couldn't have gone more smoothly and everybody had a great time!
Date night deal was quite good. Really nice, helpful, and attentive service.
Expensive. Limited menu.

Second time I’ve tried coming to this place only to find that it’s closed for a private event. What a waste of time coming all the way over here... I doubt I’ll try a third time. You guys should really find a way to more effectively share your open hours with customers.
I'm pleased with the customer service.and the food was tasty fresh and appealing.
Horrible quality steaks. Great cocktails. Nice ambience.

I had my wedding reception at La Brasa. It was an amazing evening, the staff was extremely helpful throughout the process. All of my wedding guests were so happy that the food was amazing and so different from any other weddings they’ve attended. As a bride, I felt so well taken care of by the restaurant. Absolutely love La Brasa! And I will continue to go back regularly for food 😄

The ambiance and decor of the restaurant are fine, but the food and wine are quite expensive. In addition, the taste, at least for the meal I ordered, was unsatisfactory in relation to its cost. I ordered the wood roasted chicken. The plate was relatively small, and though the chicken was spicy, it was not that flavorful.

Wonderful night dining at La Brassa, met executive chef and owner. Very warm, welcoming staff, and atmosphere, especially with large wood fired oven!!! Food was amazing. Combinations of unique flavors in every starter and entree. Awesome experience. Looking forward to my brother's wedding there this winter!!!
Great food, pleasant ambiance,  and very nice staff.
Brunch's midichlorian count is off the charts
Pretty good food, although very pricey, for example, the $50 t bone comes with no sides. Our server barely talked and didn't seem happy to be there.
Great food, neat atmosphere

Left pretty unimpressed. The prices are quite high for the food. The sweet potato starter was very good, and the baked chicken was juicy. Their whole idea is small plates, which is fine, but they’re super expensive. The service was fine but not outstanding. Also, their house-made ginger beer was undrinkable.

La Brasa is a gem!! We came here last night for the 7th or 8th time, it's the perfect place for a date night, celebration, or to bring visiting out of towners. The decor is warm and rustic, super Somervillian. The staff are AMAZING - knowledgable, friendly, patient. The food is amazing - the baked pancake at brunch changed my world, and I've replicated the sweet potato dish at home several times yet it's never as good. Also GREAT cocktails. I nearly had my wedding reception here, and I'm sure it would have been awesome. La Brasa is somehow cozy enough for 2 and spacious enough for a party of 8. Can't wait to go back!!

Servers are excellent, and food is better.

I was pleasantly surprised by our dinner here. While reading the menu, I was ready to dislike the somewhat pretentious sounding dishes: individual chicken wings with snails, 5 dollar street-style tacos, and etc.  We ended up getting a medley of food to try, and it was a fun experiment in flavors.  One of the items was table-side prime rib, sliced by a very knowledgeable and friendly staff member.  My favorite dish was the salmon which sat on top of a delicious salad of Thai basil and other fresh tasting greens and fruits. I enjoyed our dinner here, and I would highly recommend it!
Cozy garden yard interior 👌
Great meat and yummy brazilean salads!

The $1 oyster deal drew us here. Oysters were good, but the rest of the dishes were only okay and overpriced. The potatoes could've been really good, but they were oversalted. The vegetarian tacos were not great and definitely not worth it at $5 each. Didn't try the drinks, but would consider coming back for a cocktail since the atmosphere is so nice. Service was also attentive and quick (though we felt slightly judged for not ordering more).

The service was very good.but the price of draft beer is over priced!!! Not worth coming back to the La Brasa!!!
Really cool design amd vibe inside the restaurant. Eat there to try a new spin on Mediterranean but prepare to spend a little more. Its worth it.
Managed to have a great brunch on a new year's day stomach.
Very eclectic and interesting menu that definitely a fun time especially for a group. Not every dish is a hit but you won't leave disappointed overall. Buzzy, cool vibe and really nice cocktails too.

Pretty solid grilled meats and other Mexican-inspired dishes. Service is prompt and friendly, and the drink we got (Ryan Gosling's Tears) was incredible and unique, with the toasted pine nuts really adding something special. The Mexican fried rice was forgettable but the lamb chop was really tasty without all that "gamey" flavor usually found with lamb. Flan for dessert was a highlight, with a lovely egg-y flavor.
Food was great, service was poor for a pre-planned dinner party where the waitress had no clue what our $100 dinner included and she never brought dessert.  Food was excellent!

Never go there I was with my friends there one of them have an accident to witch i excuse myself and ask the lady the was serving us to clean for them she politely say not and one of the servers was talking behind saying racist and ugly stuff about us funny thing is the I’m Spanish and I understand everything that the server say I spoke to the manager in front of him and he act like he didn’t care about it worst place to go to be honest I grow up I’m Somerville but I would not rocoment this place to anybody

Amazing! Food, service, drinks,atmosphere.... they really have their stuff together.  I had as Moscow mule they put jalapenos in the ginger beer to give it an extra kick! I tried several items on the menu and everything was fantastic. The skirt steak was a taste of heaven ..... no sauce needed the season is like a vacation for you're taste buds....I will be back for sure.
great food and drink but service was slow from waitstaff

Cool vibe, great cocktails.
Love it. Beautiful open kitchen. Delicious food.

Worst service I have had in a restaurant for a very long time.  Our reservation was at 7:15pm  and when we arrived at 7:17pm and realized there was no table available for our group, we got yelled at for not being on time by a very condescending woman. 2 minutes late at a restaurant still feels really on time.  Our table did not become available before 7:45pm i.e. 30 minutes after the reservation time so we asked if the restaurant could do something nice about it and eventually pay for the drinks we ordered at the bar while waiting. Once again the waitress was extremely rude and talked down to us saying we should expect restaurant to be busy on Saturday and calling one of the guest out for being a “babe” in a very condescending way.  The manager didn’t care at all about our situation despite our complains and stayed seated at the bar gossiping about us in a very unprofessional manner.  I would not recommend this place to anyone who expects to be treated nicely at a restaurant.

Delicious wood-fired Mexican cuisine,  in a stylish open kitchen restaurant make this a Somerville standout.  Chef Daniel Bojorquez never fails to surprise me with his flavors.  Portion sizes and prices are good, service is amazing and please try the fried-chicken because it is amazing!
That pork...
Great low key restaurant in a new area, definitely get small plates to share!
Lovely atmosphere, open face wood motif. Incentive combinations for flavor combinations. Today, is trying the brunch for the first time... Wish me luck
Casual, nice ambiance, delicious grilled meats, juicy burgers and nice service.
Great food and service! Had the 1$ oysters that are available 5-6pm daily. Recommend the mushroom quesadilla and duck entree!!

Wicked good cocktails and phenomenal food. Our waitress unfortunately was blase and seemed like she would have preferred to have been anywhere else. The rest of the staff however was friendly and the food was good enough to make up for her attitude. Will definitely be back!
Expensive but good

Ordered fried potatoes and carnitas tacos. Food was OK at best - I’ve had better tacos at fast food Mexican joints. Server seemed miserable and when we asked about the mushroom dish we were told not too order them as they are “too salty.” This combined with the strange vibes led us to leave earlier then planned to get dinner elsewhere.
I’ve been here 5 times. Each meal was equally impressive. One of the best restaurants in the Boston area. Try the braised beef, with the red wine au jous.

Unique, interesting (though a bit limited) menu. Good food, we'll prepared. Mediocre service (served wrong entree to one of our party of four, disrupting the "flow" of our meal), somewhat aggressive pricing for some menu items and drinks. Overall 3.5/5
Very good food but only okay service.

We have gone here a few times for dinner/date night and keep coming back. The starters are all tapas-size and ordering a bunch is a great option if you don't want entrees.  The cocktails are numerous, and the beer list, while limited, is varied with great choices. We've had good luck getting in without yet making a reservation, but, if you're on a schedule, suggest calling ahead. It's a popular place for good reasons.
Had brunch,  expensive.
BRUNCH IS MY FAVORITE
Ask for the rib eye and other specials on the cart!
Dollar oysters from 5-6 pm, with great cocktails and wine to pair. Try the chicken wings, they are insanely good.

Good service, but too expensive for the quality provided. My girlfriend request the salmon which was over cooked. After we talk to our server about the overcooked salmon the second one was ok. Not manager interaction at all. After finishing main courses, we had to leave after we saw multiple mouses crossing thru the dining room.

Fun restaurant with some nice dishes but we probably won't go back. Overall execution was just alright. The beef in the beef tamale was a beautifully cooked slab of brisket but it was too large to be properly seasoned. In contrast, the tuna tostada had so many flavors competing that the tuna was lost. The romaine salad was very nice but the roast chicken was tiny for the price (more like a breaded chicken tender, sliced) but delicious. We loved the chicken liver mousse and we loved the fresh brown bread but the two together we're an odd pairing. The roast carrots looked good but never arrived and had to be taken off the bill, one of several missteps in service. My drink was great but the lime garnish had been cut yesterday and was starting to brown. Perhaps that's the best summary of the restaurant: great ideas but poor attention to the details of execution ultimately hurt the experience.
Brunch was spot on! Bloody Mary's amazing!  Service thumbs up!

Way over priced the drinks where small for the money . For that location I wouldn't expect those prices . Good food but the prime rib at$4 a once with nothing on the side mumm I don't know maybe I am crazy but I thought it was way over priced. I won't go again
Lovely place
The flan is amazing

Went here recently and fell in love with the place! The food was excellent, a lot of the menu isn't great for sharing and I ended up picking many dishes and trying new things. The burger was excellent and the mussles were excellent. I am personally don't like eating muscles but the flavor and bits of chorizo was soooo good. Will certainly be eating here many times in the future

Food & service excellent!

The food is delicious though a bit expensive. There are tables outside for dining.

Love love love this place. I'm addicted to the Mexican fried rice and just had the duck confit leg and it was incredible. If you are in snack mode, the tacos are legit and amazing. Fantastic wines, amaro flights. Boom.
Great environment. Excellent customer service. Melodic music. Friendly atmosphere and exceptional service.
Date night meal WOW! Excellent and very special, subtle flavors.

My feelings for this place is very mixed. The restaurant itself looks great and the staff is pretty friendly. It feels like a new restaurant that hasn't exactly figured out everything quite yet. The menu items sound pretty impressive and has some high quality ingredients. Some items were great but some not so great. The duck legs and fried rice dish were pretty spot on, but other dishes were either bland or extremely overly seasoned/salted.  Overall, it is fairly small portioned and expensive food that is attempting to be more higher-end than it is. You'll even have to pay for dinner rolls. I think with a little recipe tuning and slightly larger portions, it could be great.

The place is under-rated. The food is wonderful from start to finish. We ordered the bread (ended up ordering two orders of it in the end!), with the ash butter and the ricotta with olives to start. I ordered the seabass which was amazing to say the least and my friend ordered the rib that was going around. The waiters were attentive and were extremely punctual. The smokiness of the food was evident from their way of cooking. The dessert was delicious. Safe to say we didnt leave anything behind. I have to say though if you're a picky eater and not into trying new palates and flavours this isn't the place for you. Also, the menu is limited so make sure you've looked at it before you decide to go. Definitely would go there again!

My opinion is that they need to make a decision on whether to provide full entree menu or a full tapas menu, rather than half of each. Some stuff is good, some stuff is fine. It'll suffice for a date, but I won't be going out of my way to return.
Friendly warm staff make you feel comfortable and welcome!  The space and staff just invite you to relax and enjoy.  The food is also very good and tasty.

worm in oyster, which while not inherently dangerous, does indicate poor cleanliness and service excellence. instead of replacing and assuming accountability of the error the servers acted as if it were typical and acceptable.
kind of over priced. the food is well made, but most don't justify their price tag.

Dude... Waiter was really nice and decor was great, but the prices and portions were just dumb. Wound up going somewhere else after appetizers. The $12 octopus quesadilla app was like a 5" oily cheese quesadilla with two+/- ounces of octopus slices on top. I'll spare you the rest of the details.
Inventive food and a lovely place marred by subpar/ super slow service.
Creative and delicious food, and outstanding service.

Had the grilled octopus quesadilla, the empanada with poached egg, and the night shift whirlpool (beer). The beer and the quesadilla are worth trying if you stop by. Quite the hipster joint if your in to that kinda thing.
Get the chicken wings!  And then order everything else on the menu too.
Good food. Pleasant atmosphere.

Went there for brunch. Had a good experience, ambiance was great, so service was awesome. Pancake was a must have, rest of the meals were good. Tried the espresso and tonic, it was interesting and worth a try.
Really good food and cocktails. Liked the duck and the octopus quesadillas in particular. Clearly on the expensive side, but a great place for an occasional visit.
Great service and atmosphere/ awesome food
Much improved from a year or so ago.
Try the ash butter and ricotta breads. The branzini is great but I didn't love my lobster dish, it had to be cracked open and it was very tough to do. Fantastic wine selection.

This place is amazing especially Brunch. We have been taking all of our friends there and everyone enjoys it. Their pancake is cooked in a cast iron skillet it's so delicious and I don't like pancakes that much.
Fantastic food and service.
not enough food and too expensive
The food was excellent and the atmosphere was clean and friendly.
The staff is all very friendly and the food is fantastic! My favorites are the tacos and chicken wings!
Hipsterness aside, great funky food.
Fantastic small plates, great beer selection. Empanadas and Mexican Fried Rice highly recommended!
The food was good and the service too. The whole fish anx the Mexican rice where really good.

Food was fine. Service was so tremendously bad that all pleasant food experiences were negated. We were seated promptly and then ignored for about 40 mins (7 PM reservation, 7:40 we were asked for appetizer and small orders). We were ready to put in all orders and told to wait. Apps were delivered to our table that were not ours. We had our eggplant app delivered to a different table. Water refills were non-existent (BYOWB - bring your own water bottle!). Only one person received a refill on their beverage and a second person ordered wine that never showed up. Entree order was taken very late. Entrees were ok. Finished and sat again for a long time. Half the table was bussed. Then we declined dessert and asked for the check. Waiter came back about 10 mins later and asked if we wanted dessert. Said no just check. Check was wrong. Service trumped food. Experience was 5 for 5 bad.
Good for dinner, was underwhelmed by brunch.
Highly recommended!  You can tell the chef is passionate and dedicated to their craft!!
Parents were in town for a week and this was their favorite place I took them. Carnitas tacos and green beans are out of this world
Super tasty food at prices that you'd expect for this quality. The location is a little unusual, but worth the trek if you're looking for a trendy restaurant outside the city.
Positively surprised.
I work here I know how delicious is the food..
Only been there once, but a fine dining experience!  A detail: room temperature whisky, poured into a chilled glass. Not to mention the marvelous duck or dessert.

Best. Flan. In. Boston. You must make room for this dessert. It's not the traditional flan you normally get. It's thick, creamy and so yummy! The dash of salt is genius! As for the rest of the menu, I believe it changes every season. Carnitas taco, scallops, Mexican fried rice, yum!
Amazing food with friendly Staff.

I read a review in the paper which made me want to try it. I loved the decor which was interesting and welcoming in an upscale way surprising for the neighborhood and the background music was nice but the only upscale thing about the food was the price! I was very disappointed . I would rather go somewhere less trendy with better food.

Came for their special pop up ramen night.   They ran out of ramen quick but was able to get a bowl of their vegan ramen.  The broth was ok ands the noodles were all cooked.   Their dessert was amazing and I would definitely go back just for that!
Food was OK. Service was weird. Overpriced.
Fantastic food and amptmospere. The menu is as interesting as you make it, and the waitstaff is great at helping guide your choice. Top quality product and service.

I brought some out-of-town friends to this restaurant with very high hopes.  Given the online reviews, I was expecting an amazing meal.  However, the meal was less than stellar.  The burnt salad was ridiculously small and almost laughable.  The dressing was too heavy and made the lettuce very soggy.  We also found that the seasoning was sparse and most of the meal was flavorless.  We had a few plates that we shared - the servers asked us every 5 minutes if we wanted more food - pushing us to order more.  We were so frustrated by the lack of flavors that we left after having only a few dishes.  I am surprised by all the amazing reviews that I have read online.  In sum, this restaurant is overrated and trendy.
I like this place a lot. They have really good food. It's somewhat pricey, especially for the area. But they have $1 oysters so they are A-OK in my book. Also their decor is beautiful!!!
Awesome food/coffee and staff.

A little culinary gem in east somerville! As soon as you walk into the room, you know that you are entering a place that truly loves food. The menu is collection of carefully constructed seasonal dishes, which are all served tapas style. I'm a fan of the sharing plate because it means I get to try more dishes. The place is also a must for brunch (try the pickled eggs!) and I makes the best espresso coffees in Boston.

Came here during the East Broadway Foodie Crawl and tried the corn...soup? Not sure, it was corn, and had some liquid, mayo?, cilantro and was pretty good. Some of the corn still had the rind on the side of it, which I couldn't eat and wasn't nice.

I love this place, from the spacious dining space to the great food and cocktails. I loved the fried chicken! It was served with escargot brown butter and actually still had pieces of the escargot (that's snails if you didn't know). The cocktails are also delicious and inventive. You can't go wrong with having the bartender make you something off-menu either. Next door, they have a small coffee shop and market selling local artisanal products.

Quite good, though slightly expensive for what I was expecting. The drinks were very good (house sangria is a little different, more like a mixed drink). We had: grilled chicken, which was the most tender chicken I've ever had...almost weirdly so; the tacos, which were fantastic; lamb kebabs which were the most wood fire thing we got, and were quite good; and affogato for dessert, which wasn't the best--the coffee tasted a little too roasted or something (which was surprising given that reviews tout the excellent coffee), but was on the whole pretty good still. The waiter was a bit awkward and eager, like he's new to waiting tables, though everyone else who came to the table was pleasant. We were informed while ordering that the dining style is tapas, so be ready for smaller portions for entree prices. Ideal for a special occasion if you're looking for a more relaxed atmosphere.
